Sure, here is a simple example of how you can use pandas library in Python to read data from an Excel file (which is essentially a type of spreadsheet). 

```python
import pandas as pd

def read_spreadsheet(filepath):
    # Read the excel file into a DataFrame object
    df = pd.read_excel(filepath)
    
    return df
```
This function takes in the path to your Excel spreadsheet and returns it as a pandas DataFrame, which is essentially a 2-dimensional labeled data structure with columns of potentially different types. You can then manipulate this DataFrame using various functions provided by pandas library.
